Due to the announcement made by Governor JB Pritzker, all District 147 buildings will be closed from Tuesday, March 17, 2020 through Monday, March 30, 2020. For now, schools are scheduled to reopen on Tuesday, March 31, 2020.

We will be offering meal service for all students during this closure.

post_text:
On this final day of teacher appreciation week, I honor the staff of Lincoln Early Learning Center. These angels are responsible for our students' first impression of school. Our students are babies when they come and our teachers must truly nurture and guide them IN ADDITION TO teaching academic skills! They have to deal with tears (from both children and parents), meltdowns and fears. And let's not forget outfit changes, interesting personalities and everything else that comes with little ones!

I tell the story often of how I student taught in Kindergarten. I know FIRST HAND how difficult of a task that is and knew I could not do it! The early childhood teachers have a gift and we are so grateful they are sharing it with our WHD 147 community!

Thank You for All That You Do!

- Mrs. Miller, Superintendent of Schools

post_text:
My reflection today is on Martin Luther King Elementary School. It is a joy to visit King. High expectations are apparent - in the halls, in the classroom - throughout the entire building! The teachers at King have the awesome responsibility of helping children learn to regulate their feelings of impulsiveness, while also developing their academic and creative minds. I spent most of my teaching years as a fourth grade teacher, so I definitely understand that it is not an easy feat!

King teachers want what's best for their students and are willing to go the extra mile, try that new initiative and support the mission and goals set before them. It truly does make my job just a bit easier and for that I am grateful!

Today and all days, I celebrate my elementary staff....Thank You For All You Do! ❤

- Mrs. Miller, Superintendent of Schools

post_text:
As we kick off National Teacher's Appreciation Week, I salute the teachers of Rosa Parks Middle School. Middle School is a passage in the journey of our students' lives. The issues that middle school teachers face is like none other. Students are in the stages of evolving from children to young adults and it is a hard journey for students that do not have any issues. Compound that with the many things that our students face today and the journey is almost unbearable... or even unattainable. Our middle school teachers deal with this daily. Your hard work is not unnoticed and I appreciate all that you do!

HAPPY TEACHER'S APPRECIATION WEEK!

- Mrs. Miller, Superintendent

You can’t always see pain……

Unfortunately, the rate of attempts of suicide among adolescents and teens continues to grow at an alarming rate!

Together we can learn to recognize sadness, anxiety and depression in our students.

Together we can HELP to prevent thoughts and attempts of suicide in our school aged children.

Please join us on Wednesday,
February 20, 2019
5-6:30 p.m. at Lincoln Early Learning Center for
Superintendent’s Coffee Talk
